articles.title: Research: Exercise can cause stroke - In which people - LiFO
articles.description: A new scientific study published in the "Physics of Fluids" journal highlights the danger of acute exercise for patients with particularly blocked carotid arteries. The increased heart rate can cause a stroke in some cases. The researchers used a specialized computational model to simulate blood flow in the carotid arteries in three stages of stenosis, without obstruction, with mild obstruction of 30%, and with moderate obstruction of 50%. They compared the effect of exercise-induced heart rate of 140 beats per minute with resting heart rates of 67 and 100 beats per minute. Exercise improved the health of the simulated carotid artery for healthy and mild cases, but the results for moderate stenosis were concerning. The authors recommend regular monitoring of arterial health for individuals who engage in intense exercise and a carefully prescribed exercise program for individuals with moderate to severe stenosis or a history of stroke.

The lightning was detected by space-based optical sensors and global networks of ground-based radio antennas thousands of miles away. The research team found that the eruption produced 2,615 flashes per minute at its peak intensity, which lasted nearly five minutes.

He is renowned for his many fundamental contributions and discoveries in quantum and classical field theories, including the establishment of the presence of the famous Adler–Bell–Jackiw anomalies in quantum field theory.
